  "doc_id": "24404",
  "text": "At last, we recall that q-Gaussian distributions, in addition to provide a very powerful effective description of complex systems, have also a predictive power. For instance, [CITATION_1] proposed an experiment on optical lattices; such an experiment was later performed [CITATION_2] ) confirming the expectation. We have also proposed [CITATION_3] ) an experiment to look for a cut-off in the energy distribution of gammas in electron recombination that could confirm deviations and possibly measure the relevant parameter of the distribution. To obtain predictive results in the astrophysics and space science field is the challenge of the next future.",
